title: Registry Modifications Related to LockBitv3 Ransomware
id: cbb30fd3-b91a-4814-b79a-55e020393203
status: experimental
description: Detects modifying registry keys to enable smart screen, allow auto logon, and disable Windows Event Logging.
references:
 - https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa22-181a
 - https://www.picussecurity.com/resource/medusalocker-ransomware-analysis-simulation-and-mitigation
author: Tyler Casey @1qazCasey, @scythe_io
date: 2023/12/21
tags:
  - attack.T1547
  - attack.T1059
logsource:
 product: windows
 service: sysmon
detection:
 selection_base:
   EventID: 13
 selection1:
   TargetObject|contains:
     - '*\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\MSFEEditor*'
   Details: '*.exe'
 selection2:
   TargetObject|contains:
     - '*\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\System\EnabledLinkConnections'
   Details: '1'
 condition: selection_base and (selection1 or selection2)
falsepositives:
 - Legitimate system administration tasks may use similar commands.
level: high
